The coronavirus has been a burden to everyone across the world. This is a virus that has brought the world to a standstill with economies globally reeling from the negative effects of the pandemic. Kenya on Friday recorded 23 new cases of Covid-19, raising the country's total number to 781, Health CAS Rashid Aman has said. This is out of the 2,100 samples that were tested in the last 24 hours. 11 of the cases were from Nairobi, Mombasa (5), Kajiado (3) with Kiambu and Wajir with two each. Kenyans have been asked by the government to turn up for voluntary testing as they continue fighting the pandemic and curbing further spread. You might not know the procedure used to test for the virus, but these photos will shed some light on the process;